<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-194] httpClient does not support installation of different SSLSocketFactory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-194</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>Description:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The SSLProtocolSocketFactory class had hard-&lt;br/&gt;
coded &amp;quot;javax.net.ssl.SSLSocketFactory&amp;quot; as the socket factory.  It does not &lt;br/&gt;
support installation of other socket factory.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Proposed Fix:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We added a setDefaultSSLSocketFactory method to the SSLProtocolSocketFactory &lt;br/&gt;
and modified the code to use the factory it it is set.  The code falls back on &lt;br/&gt;
using &amp;quot;javax.net.ssl.SSLSocketFactory&amp;quot; if a default is not set.</description>
                <environment>Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other</environment>
